cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of explaining the behavior of machine learning models, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The specific focus of the paper is on learning vector quantization models, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper proposes different types of convex and non-convex programs, which are commonly used in optimization problems in neural networks (cs.NE).
